reviews.review_text:
Like the other fellow, I hope I'm not in the minority! Unlike apparently, the other two reviewers, I was at this show. Although some of the versions were not that great, I was very happy with the song list, as well as the day before. At least the rarer tunes, (besides those), I'd agree to some extent, ie. I'd been yawnin' at the generic tunes for years by this point, therefore virtually any rare/different tunes were welcome to me. Obviously we have different taste.     However it's been a while since I listened to this and I haven't many times. Moreover, I was quite lucky given my circumstances to be able to attend any shows at this time, hence that could skew my perception. So I'm going to recheck it!

     Augy

     San Diego

Aiding amateur musicians Great sound and not bad performance.  In fact using the great up tempo on this version of brown eyed women to work on our band's cover arrangement.  Mandolin, acoustic bass, guitar and on percussion, washboard tie

Of Course,I was there! I was getting down & freaky in the isle,slightly to right of soundboard,on Jerry's side.Jerry loving his new Cripe(Lighting Bolt}The band is firing on all cylinders,right from the start.Thank you Charlie Miller.Listen loud.#dontletgo

THe entire year Healy couldn't fix Billy's bad kick drum mic cable? Every single 93 show soundboard features Billiy with a bad cable on his kick drum. Healy sucked. He ruined so many good nights with poor sound, messing with Bob's vocals, keeping gates on the mics with the threshold set too low, cutting off the first words of lines. (Bertha 8-22-93) There was some good playing in 93, but no soundboards are listenable due to a rookie mistake of not keeping on top of your cabling.

I won tickets to these hometown SD shows from a radio station. They were going to give it to the 10th caller, but me and a buddy called them and said it would be much better publicity if we could offer to be publicly humiliated for the tickets. The station took me up on it, and I received a call at my work with the Mission Impossible theme music playing when I answered. They directed me and a friend to the mall to try on woman's lingerie. The lady who helped us was horrified. I chose a more modest feathery thing but my buddy went full on tight red teddy!. Classic stuff. The show was fun but we could tell Jerry was slipping up and he only got worse in LA the following week.
